article.description: Xavier Moon scored 14 points, DeJuan Marrero added 11 while pulling down 12 rebounds, and Morehead State held on for a 70-67 win over Eastern Kentucky on Saturday night.
article.headline: Morehead State hangs on for 70-67 win over Eastern Kentucky
article.linkText: Morehead State hangs on for 70-67 win over Eastern Kentucky
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. -- Xavier Moon scored 14 points, DeJuan Marrero added 11 while pulling down 12 rebounds, and Morehead State held on for a 70-67 win over Eastern Kentucky on Saturday night. Morehead State (12-9, 6-3 Ohio Valley Conference) retook the lead during an 11-0 run that included a 3-pointer from Malik Maitland to go up 43-38 with 14:07 left. The Eagles never trailed again but had to hold off an Eastern Kentucky surge that cut a seven-point deficit and tied the game at 62 when Nick Mayo sank a pair of free throws with 2:15 remaining. Brent Arrington then hit a 3-pointer at the other end and Morehead State sealed it with 5-for-10 shooting from the foul line down the stretch. Anthony Elechi had 12 points and Lyonell Gaines 10 for the Eagles. Mayo's 19 points led the Colonels (12-12, 3-6), who were just 1 of 17 from 3-point range.
